This will be primarily focused on SMW because corny had total creative control. I dont know what he booked in 89 WCW. But I will delve into other stuff as well. This one usually draws some heat lol

CHARACTERS / ROSTER 9/10 - Cornette obviously played himself as the heat drawing heel manager with his stable (and he is a great manager). He had bob armstrong in there as the babyface commissioner. He had proven ( especially in his territory) but worn draws like the rockin roll express constantly fueding with teams like the heavenly bodies. His main heel champ was tony anthony, who was a pretty good worker and good heel. He had the gangstas which was great btw. Brian lee, Tim horner (lol). Cornette has a good eye for talent too. He brought in guys like jericho and storm, glenn jacobs and bob holly. People like too give him credit for scouting brock, cena, and orton from OVW but that place was a wwf feeder system and where else were they supposed too work stateside? SMW also had a working agreement as a feeder for WWF and corny could bring in SCSA or shawn michaels or whoever too sell some extra tickets. They also had guys coming "in between" jobs from wcw or wwf. SMW had many terrible wrestlers as well like boo bradley or the tru to the crew guy. He could also get amazing vets like bobby eaton or terry funk in there. Various amounts of mullets, beer bellies, and armstrong family members flying around. He even had based commentators like dutch mantell and great refs like mark curtis. Having tons of connections and a good eye for talent he managed too keep a pretty great roster.

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com: GIMMICKS 7/10 - Going too start with the bad here but the SMW mummy and the ninja turtle gimmick were pretty bad. For a guy who wants such a ridiculous business to be taken seriously, this stuff is just bad. I dont care if rick rubin wanted it or not, jim booked it and it ultimately falls on him. He didnt have rubin in OVW but he had batista pretending to be a demon or some shit. He gave people ill fitting gimmicks too like why would you give bob holly a "hollwood" gimmick. I know its because his last name is holly but still that was fucking stupid. Now for the good. The gangstas gimmick was awesome lol. New Jack just laying into a bunch of rednecks was hilarious. And the two count for affirmative action was brilliant. Fried chicken and watermelons too KEK. Ron wright as the top heel manager was dimes. Him in that fucking wheelchair too collect fake disability too piss off all the blue collar dudes in the crowd was great. Ron wright was a heat magnet. Sunny as a hillary clinton type character was great as well. Jim knew that fans in that area would despise a good looking, college educated democrat. Pretty brilliant stuff and jimmy definitely knew how too book heat in that territory. Also, even though Kane was originally pritchards idea, cornette making him an unstoppable michael myers type character was dimes and that was all corny. Hell in the cell was dope too.

ANGLES / STORYLINES / STYLE 5/10 - He didnt put many angles in his shows. Angles were far and few between on shows because he didnt want too "hotshot". This is always an excuse for lazy booking too me. Cornette is a true historian, and used the same old promoter tricks that had been used forever. Champ keeps running out of the ring for a countout, lumberjack match. Heel gets outside interference, cage match. Piledriver bans, fines, ether rags and hair vs hair matches. Stuff that has been done too death. I know he does this shit because " it makes sense", but he is trying too make sense out of a business that makes no sense at all. Its a fake fight where everybody knows its fake excluding 5 year olds and retards. I dont know why guys like him cling so hard too this stuff. I watched SMW when I was young, I have watched some of it for this review. 95 percent of it is boring with with lazy ass veterans exchanging rest holds. Good promos from many guys, but its just boring too watch.

OVERALL 21/30

I will say I also think russo is good at knowing how too push people properly ( even if he doesnt know who too push) and making it stick. His 98 storyline push of the rock too corporate world champion was masterful..and long before triple h his "friend" married stephanie russo morphed him from the DX leader too violent heel double crosser, mastermind strategist that was obsessed with the WWF title. russo is good at gimmicks, and my proof is val venis. posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
ANGLES / STORYLINES/ STYLE 8/10 - trying to keep this to a paragraph which is difficult. russo IS storylines and angles. There are thousands too mention, some good some bad. He would keep matches as short as possible and drown his shows with non stop angles and bullshit. He has defended this by saying "the masses" want too see episodic TV and I personally think he is kind of right. Crash TV is a style he and ferrera developed and russo kind of has the formula/ structure of it down too a science. Thats the thing about russo, despite all the madness he does have a method too it. That method only works however when he has wrestlers who actually showed up for backstage pretapes and production crews/ editors that werent totally moronic (see wcw). He booked many great storylines, and his booking of the austin mcmahon fued was the one of the key elements too turning the tables on wcws run. Yes he had austin, the rock, undertaker and foley etc. but mcmahon had those guys in 96 and was doing fuck all with half of them. Another thing about russo that I liked is everybody had a storyline, even the jabronis on sunday night heat had fueds. He paid attention to everyone on the roster ... not just the top dogs. He had his share of really stupid storylines as well. Like the thing where he wanted bagwell to do the job but bagwell disagreed and " won" screwing over the powers that be. He always wanted too make a behind the scenes show about the business, that stuff just did not transslate well on nitro. The arquette shit was dumb too but people over blow it honestly. He loves swerves, but when something happens that fans dont expect it genuinely shocking. when you swerve just too swerve it loses its shock factor.

OVERALL 24/30
